    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Matthew",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 7,
        "summary": "Jesus concludes the Sermon on the Mount\u2014He commands, Judge not; ask of God; beware of false prophets\u2014He promises salvation to those who do the will of the Father.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "Judge not, that ye be not judged.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a0Matt. 7:1\u20132 Now these are the words which Jesus taught his disciples that they should say unto the people. Judge not unrighteously, that ye be not judged; but judge righteous judgment. Alma 41:14 (14\u201315); 3\u00a0Ne. 14:1 (1\u201327); D&C 11:12.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 5
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Accountability.",
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 32
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For with what judgment ye judge, ye shall be judged: and with what measure ye mete, it shall be measured to you again.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Judgment.",
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 22
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 11:25; D&C 1:10.",
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 74
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Esth. 7:10; 1\u00a0Ne. 14:3; D&C 10:26 (25\u201327).",
                        "start": 96,
                        "end": 104
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And why beholdest thou the mote that is in thy brother's eye, but considerest not the beam that is in thine own eye?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a0Matt. 7:4\u20138 (Appendix).",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 3
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0speck, chip, or splinter. TG\u00a0Gossip.",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 31
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "The Greek word refers to a wooden beam used in constructing houses.",
                        "start": 86,
                        "end": 90
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Or how wilt thou say to thy brother, Let me pull out the mote out of thine eye; and, behold, a beam is in thine own eye?",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 100,
                        "end": 102
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Thou hypocrite, first cast out the beam out of thine own eye; and then shalt thou see clearly to cast out the mote out of thy brother's eye.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Hypocrisy.",
                        "start": 5,
                        "end": 14
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Give not that which is holy unto the dogs, neither cast ye your pearls before swine, lest they trample them under their feet, and turn again and rend you.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a0Matt. 7:9\u201311 (Appendix).",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 4
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Holiness; Sacred; Sacrilege.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 27
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 23:9; Matt. 15:26 (26\u201328); D&C 6:12 (10\u201312); 10:37 (36\u201337); 41:6.",
                        "start": 64,
                        "end": 70
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Ask, and it shall be given you; seek, and ye shall find; knock, and it shall be opened unto you:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a0Matt. 7:12\u201317 (Appendix). Isa. 58:9 (8\u20139); Hel. 10:5 (4\u201311); D&C 6:5. TG\u00a0Faith; God, Access to; Prayer; Problem-Solving.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 3
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Revelation.",
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 26
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Meditation; Objectives; Study.",
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 36
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Learn.",
                        "start": 57,
                        "end": 62
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For every one that asketh receiveth; and he that seeketh findeth; and to him that knocketh it shall be opened.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Education.",
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 56
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Or what man is there of you, whom if his son ask bread, will he give him a stone?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Bread.",
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 54
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Or if he ask a fish, will he give him a serpent?",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "If ye then, being evil, know how to give good gifts unto your children, how much more shall your Father which is in heaven give good things to them that ask him?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0although you are wicked.",
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 22
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore all things whatsoever ye would that men should do to you, do ye even so to them: for this is the law and the prophets.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Good Works.",
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 31
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Marriage, Continuing Courtship in.",
                        "start": 46,
                        "end": 49
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 15:15 (12\u201315); Prov. 24:29. TG\u00a0Citizenship; Courtesy; Kindness.",
                        "start": 57,
                        "end": 59
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Benevolence.",
                        "start": 68,
                        "end": 70
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Law of Moses.",
                        "start": 107,
                        "end": 110
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 1198
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Enter ye in at the strait gate: for wide is the gate, and broad is the way, that leadeth to destruction, and many there be which go in thereat:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0narrow; see also 2\u00a0Ne. 31:17\u201321.",
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 25
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 13:24; 3\u00a0Ne. 27:33; D&C 22:4 (1\u20134); 43:7.",
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 30
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 132:25. TG\u00a0Hell.",
                        "start": 92,
                        "end": 103
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 43
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 64,
                        "end": 66
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Because strait is the gate, and narrow is the way, which leadeth unto life, and few there be that find it.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 3:17.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 14
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 8:20 (19\u201324); 2\u00a0Ne. 33:9. TG\u00a0Baptism, Essential.",
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 26
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jer. 21:8.",
                        "start": 70,
                        "end": 74
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 17
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 41
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Beware of false prophets, which come to you in sheep's clothing, but inwardly they are ravening wolves.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0False Prophets.",
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 24
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Sheep.",
                        "start": 47,
                        "end": 54
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Hypocrisy.",
                        "start": 69,
                        "end": 77
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Guile.",
                        "start": 96,
                        "end": 102
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Ye shall know them by their fruits. Do men gather grapes of thorns, or figs of thistles?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0recognize, detect. TG\u00a0Discernment, Spiritual.",
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 13
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 20:11; Jer. 28:9 (8\u20139); Luke 6:44; Moro. 7:6 (5\u201317). TG\u00a0Good Works.",
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 34
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Even so every good tree bringeth forth good fruit; but a corrupt tree bringeth forth evil fruit.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "The Greek wording carries the meaning of beautiful, precious fruit without blemish.",
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 43
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 12:33; 3\u00a0Ne. 14:20 (17\u201320).",
                        "start": 44,
                        "end": 49
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0decayed, rotten, stale.",
                        "start": 57,
                        "end": 64
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0bad, spoiled, degenerate.",
                        "start": 85,
                        "end": 89
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "A good tree cannot bring forth evil fruit, neither can a corrupt tree bring forth good fruit.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 51,
                        "end": 54
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Every tree that bringeth not forth good fruit is hewn down, and cast into the fire.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 3:9; John 15:2 (1\u20136); Jacob 5:26 (26\u201360); Alma 5:36; D&C 97:7.",
                        "start": 40,
                        "end": 45
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 13:7.",
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 53
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Wherefore by their fruits ye shall know them.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "James 2:18 (14\u201326); 1\u00a0Jn. 3:10 (10\u201318).",
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 25
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Not every one that saith unto me, Lord, Lord, shall enter into the kingdom of heaven; but he that doeth the will of my Father which is in heaven.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Titus 1:16. TG\u00a0Hypocrisy; Sincere.",
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 24
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Hosea 8:2 (1\u20134); Luke 6:46.",
                        "start": 34,
                        "end": 38
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 8:21 (9\u201321); D&C 138:4. TG\u00a0Duty; Good Works; Obedience.",
                        "start": 98,
                        "end": 103
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Will of.",
                        "start": 108,
                        "end": 112
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a0Matt. 7:30\u201331 \u2026 heaven. For the day soon cometh, that men shall come before me to judgment, to be judged according to their works.",
                        "start": 138,
                        "end": 144
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Many will say to me in that day, Lord, Lord, have we not prophesied in thy name? and in thy name have cast out devils? and in thy name done many wonderful works?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jer. 23:25 (25\u201332). TG\u00a0Unrighteous Dominion.",
                        "start": 57,
                        "end": 67
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 84:67. TG\u00a0Name.",
                        "start": 92,
                        "end": 96
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And then will I profess unto them, I never knew you: depart from me, ye that work iniquity.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a0Matt. 7:33 And then will I say, Ye never knew me \u2026 Ps. 101:4; Matt. 25:12; Mosiah 26:27 (23\u201327); 3\u00a0Ne. 14:23.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 3
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 119:115. TG\u00a0Judgment, the Last.",
                        "start": 53,
                        "end": 59
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0lawlessness. TG\u00a0Sin.",
                        "start": 82,
                        "end": 90
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore whosoever heareth these sayings of mine, and doeth them, I will liken him unto a wise man, which built his house upon a rock:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 4:10; Hel. 5:12 (9\u201312); D&C 41:5.",
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 27
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Commitment; Obedience.",
                        "start": 55,
                        "end": 60
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0he will resemble.",
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 68
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Wisdom.",
                        "start": 91,
                        "end": 95
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 6:34; 11:24.",
                        "start": 107,
                        "end": 112
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0the rock. 3\u00a0Ne. 11:39 (39\u201340).",
                        "start": 128,
                        "end": 134
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the rain descended, and the floods came, and the winds blew, and beat upon that house; and it fell not: for it was founded upon a rock.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 90:5.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 12
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Adversity.",
                        "start": 69,
                        "end": 73
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Rock.",
                        "start": 134,
                        "end": 138
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And every one that heareth these sayings of mine, and doeth them not, shall be likened unto a foolish man, which built his house upon the sand:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Foolishness.",
                        "start": 94,
                        "end": 101
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the rain descended, and the floods came, and the winds blew, and beat upon that house; and it fell: and great was the fall of it.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 14:11.",
                        "start": 84,
                        "end": 89
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Apostasy of Individuals.",
                        "start": 98,
                        "end": 102
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 1199
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And it came to pass, when Jesus had ended these sayings, the people were astonished at his doctrine:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a0Matt. 7:36 \u2026 these sayings with his disciples, the people\u00a0\u2026",
                        "start": 42,
                        "end": 67
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 13:54.",
                        "start": 73,
                        "end": 83
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "John 7:16; 2\u00a0Ne. 31:21.",
                        "start": 91,
                        "end": 99
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For he taught them as one having authority, and not as the scribes.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a0Matt. 7:37 \u2026 authority from God, and not as having authority from the scribes. TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Authority of; Jesus Christ, Teaching Mode of; Teaching with the Spirit.",
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 42
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0their scribes. TG\u00a0Scribe.",
                        "start": 55,
                        "end": 66
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 25
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
}